Name: hydrogen
Desc: The lightest element of the periodic table, Hydrogen is the most abundant chemical substance in the Universe

Name: helium
Desc: Helium is a colorless, odorless, tasteless non-toxic gas. The first of the noble gases, Helium has the lowest boiling point of all the elements

Name: lithium
Desc: A highly flammable and reactive element, lithium is the lightest solid element in the table.

Name: beryllium
Desc: Beryllium is one of the rarest elements in the Universe. It is a gray, brittle alkaline metal.

Name: boron
Desc: Boron is  very low in abundance in the Universe, as it is only created as result of cosmic rays and supernoave.

Name: carbon
Desc: A highly flammable and reactive element, lithium is the lightest solid element in the table.

Name: nitrogen
Desc: A common element of life on Earth, carbon is nonmetallic and has the unique ability to form different organic compounds, such as graphite as diamonds

Name: oxygen
Desc: A member of the chalcogen group of the periodic table, oxygen is a highlyreactive nonmetal that is the 3rd most abundant element in the Universe.

Name: fluorine
Desc: The lightest of the halogens, fluorine is a higly toxic gas, and is used commerically in electric insulators and refrigerants

Name: neon
Desc: Under standard conditions, neon is a colorless, odorless, and inert gas. A rare gas, it was disovered to be one of three residual elements left in dry air after removing nitrogen, oxygen, argon, and  carbon dioxide

Name: sodium
Desc: Sodium is a soft, white, highly reactive metal that is present is various numerals, such as feldspars and rock salts. Sodium compounds are widely used, such as sodium chloride (table salt).

Name: magnesium
Desc: A siny, gray metal, magnesium is produced in older stars as well as exploding supernovae. It is the fourth most common element in the Earth, compsoing a significant portion of the planet's mantle
